&gt; I for one would not have any interest in a &quot;certification&quot; program
or any fee involved with one. I do believe a fee for direct expenses
such as meeting room, coffee, equipment rental, gas expenses for the
coordinator etc. is not only appropirate but esential for a group
meeting. I also heartedly believe that a small fee for direct
expenses is important for demonstratingappreciation of value on the
part of participants. If zero is paid, it&#39;s too easy to say &quot;yes, I&#39;m
in&quot; and then never show.The money is a token. That&#39;s been my
experience.But that&#39;s just me. ron
